Settings

You can change the following items under Settings.

Battle Settings

• Support Ability Order
You can set the order in which support characters' abilities will be displayed.

Support Ability Order


• Enemy HP Percentage Display
You can choose to display or hide the percentage of enemies' remaining HP.

• Party Member Details Display
You can adjust the display settings for party members' details in battle.

Party Member Details Display


• Battle Log Display
You can adjust the settings for battle log display.

Battle Log Display



Sound
You can change the volume for BGM (background music), SE (sound effects), and voices.

• Continuous Burst Mode BGM
You can set whether or not the burst mode BGM continues even after burst mode ends.

• Continuous Summoning BGM
You can set whether or not the summoning BGM continues even after summoning ends.


Draw Auto-Sale
　You can set up automatic sale of 3★ and 4★ gear obtained in draws.

　*Note that gil obtained from automatic sale in excess of the maximum amount that can be held (9,999,999) will be lost.
　
　
Push Notifications
You can set whether or not to receive general announcements or notifications for when your SP/Link Bell recovers.

Power Settings
You can adjust your power settings to conserve battery power.
